  "prompt": "What can you buy with 4.95 canadian dollars on the Internet that's worth it?",
  "response": "With a budget of $4.95 CAD, you can find a variety of small but potentially worthwhile items on the Internet. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **eBooks or Digital Content:** Many online platforms offer eBooks for less than $5. Sites like Amazon Kindle, Google Books, or Kobo often have deals on popular titles or classics.\n\n2. **Mobile App Purchases:** You can use this budget to buy apps, games, or in-app purchases on platforms like the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n\n3. **Online Subscription Trials:** Many streaming services or digital content platforms offer limited-time trials for a month or a week that fit within this budget. For example, Spotify, Apple Music, or various news websites may have introductory offers.\n\n4. **Music or Video Downloads:** Sites like iTunes or Google Play often offer individual songs, albums, or movie rentals at prices below $5.\n\n5. **Printable Art or Craft Patterns:** Websites like Etsy offer digital downloads for printable art, craft patterns, or planners that you can buy within your budget.\n\n6. **Discounted Humble Bundle or Steam Sales:** Occasionally you may find games or game bundles on sale on platforms like Steam or Humble Bundle for less than $5.\n\nTo get the best value, searching for deals or sale items specific to your interests is recommended.",
